title: Grain mostly lower, livestock lower
text:
Thu, Aug 27, 2015, 3:18 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 6 hrs 42 mins Grain mostly lower, livestock lower Grain mostly lower on the CBOT, beef lower and pork lower on the CME Associated Press â€“ 2 hours 48 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly lower in early trading Wednesday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery lost 2.50 cents to $4.97 a bushel; December corn was 1.25 cents lower at $3.7820 a bushel; December oats were 2 cents lower at 2.1720 a bushel; while November soybeans lost 2.25 cents to 8.7540 a bushel. 
Beef lower and pork were lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .33 cent lower at $1.4138 a pound; October feeder cattle was 1.20 cents lower at $1.9455 a pound; October lean hogs lost .38 cent to $.6713 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Terms
